<br>
I think the number of people that visit this forum is unfortunately way overestimated. Don't count on everyone on the server:<br>
<br>
a) Visiting the FV board<br>
b) Realizing this forum exists<br>
c) Caring enough that it exists to enter it<br>
d) Reading anything in the forum<br>
e) Reading the specific post of the raid you are leading/hoping to attend<br>
f) Caring ( this is where they become jerks )<br>
<br>
Honestly, we would not have planned to go to Fear if we knew there was an open raid planned. However, you can't begrudge someone for not knowing. It's not always a matter of &quot;knowing and not caring&quot;, it's most often a matter of &quot;having no idea that someone else wished to kill what you wanted to kill two days after you, and killing it because no one else was there killing it&quot;.<br>
<br>
FV has no reservation system, and this forum is most definately not one. It was asked above what purpose this forum had, if not to reserve. The simple answer is: to get the word out to those that attend open raids that you are having one, in an attempt to gain their help. You can't reasonably expect more from this forum than that. I used to, and after similar things as this have happened with targets I wanted for my guild, I have realized it's just not possible. It sucks. I know first hand, but it's how things happen sometimes. I have learned to shrug it off, because it is really no one's fault. It's disappointing, for sure, but we don't really have anyone to blame.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am sorry that your raid won't work out, guys. I hope you can get to Fear soon and get all the items that you need. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
